1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:03,895
Brock, what are you doing?

2
00:00:04,505 --> 00:00:06,997
Getting ready for
surgery. What's it look like?

3
00:00:07,207 --> 00:00:09,039
You're operating on my sister.

4
00:00:09,943 --> 00:00:12,435
And my fiancÃ©e.

5
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:14,243
You're drunk.
You could kill her.

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:18,452
It's the only way to stop
my hands from shaking.

7
00:00:18,552 --> 00:00:19,884
I need to drink.

8
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:22,485
For Anna.

9
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:25,492
What about our baby?

10
00:00:26,260 --> 00:00:28,229
Our baby?

11
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:38,103
Brock! Oh, my God! Brock, are
you okay? Brock, speak to me.

12
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:42,835
Oh, my God! I
think he's really hurt.

13
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:44,037
Cut!

14
00:00:47,981 --> 00:00:50,221
That was scary. I thought
for a second you were really...

15
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:53,311
Then you're going to be the
only one in the world who did.

16
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:55,712
This is ridiculous.

17
00:00:55,789 --> 00:00:56,789
That was great, Evan.

18
00:00:56,857 --> 00:00:58,086
No, it wasn't. It was crap.

19
00:00:58,158 --> 00:00:59,387
The fans are going to love it.

20
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:01,155
The fans are crap. I'm crap.

21
00:01:01,261 --> 00:01:04,095
This whole damn show is crap!

22
00:01:04,164 --> 00:01:06,030
Sorry, not your fault.

23
00:01:37,798 --> 00:01:41,200
Where are you going? My
apartment's on the West Side.

24
00:01:41,301 --> 00:01:44,032
Excuse me, you need
to go the other way.

25
00:01:45,272 --> 00:01:46,968
Hey, did you hear what I said?

26
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:55,514
What the hell's going on
here? What do you want?

27
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:58,612
An autographed
picture would be nice.

28
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,613
Oh, and I'm also
going to save your life.

29
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,860
You might want to think about
repositioning the crosswalk.

30
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:51,063
It's technically not a violation, but
the closer they are to the entrance,

31
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:52,730
the more likely
they are to be used.

32
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:54,104
Makes sense.

33
00:02:54,207 --> 00:02:56,699
Listen, I actually wasn't
expecting you until next month.

34
00:02:56,777 --> 00:03:00,270
Yeah, that's the problem with planned
visits, administrators plan for them.

35
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:05,077
The most recent New Jersey
Hospital Accreditation requirements.

36
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,785
Yeah, I'm familiar with...

37
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:16,229
Who is that?

38
00:03:17,064 --> 00:03:20,034
I have no idea.
Shall we get started?

39
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:27,741
Just let me go. I won't press
charges. I'll forget the whole thing.

40
00:03:27,808 --> 00:03:30,300
That's probably true, seeing
as how you have a brain tumor.

41
00:03:32,412 --> 00:03:35,177
You're that nut-job doctor
that keeps calling my publicist.

42
00:03:35,282 --> 00:03:37,911
Actually, I'm the nut-job
Head of Diagnostic Medicine.

43
00:03:37,984 --> 00:03:42,115
I run every day. I don't get headaches.
I'm fine. So, if you don't mind...

44
00:03:42,189 --> 00:03:43,851
Actually, I do mind.

45
00:03:43,957 --> 00:03:47,450
I don't care if you die,
but if Brock Sterling dies,

46
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:50,929
Anna never finds out he's
the father of Marie's baby.

47
00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:52,423
Help!

48
00:03:52,499 --> 00:03:53,762
Help!

49
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:56,930
We're gonna need
a wheelchair here!

50
00:03:57,871 --> 00:03:59,533
Look, in the last month,

51
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:03,599
your average line reading has
slowed from 2.1 seconds to 2.9.

52
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:05,679
You're pausing more,
always at the same interval,

53
00:04:05,779 --> 00:04:07,441
every seven to nine words,

54
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:10,348
which means you're having trouble
reading one side of the teleprompter,

55
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,861
which means a
peripheral vision problem,

56
00:04:11,885 --> 00:04:15,014
which means a tumor
in your occipital lobe.

57
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:20,457
Just one test. If there's nothing
wrong, I'll take you right back home.

58
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,861
Make it cab fare. I don't want
you anywhere near my house.

59
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:35,900
Just put it in my spot.

60
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:40,071
The Accreditation Board is here
to protect us and our patients.

61
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:42,809
So, in dealing with
the onsite inspector,

62
00:04:42,883 --> 00:04:47,412
please behave as if it wasn't also an
enormous pain in the ass. Thank you.

63
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:50,687
Chase, Foreman,
Cameron, up here, please.

64
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,420
Why is House driving a limo?

65
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:58,522
Don't know. Don't have to know.

66
00:04:58,598 --> 00:05:00,533
Don't care. CUDDY: Wrong.

67
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,229
Until this inspection is over
you're back on House-watch.

68
00:05:03,336 --> 00:05:04,531
Current case. Past cases.

69
00:05:04,604 --> 00:05:05,648
He doesn't have a current case.

70
00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:06,833
I have a whole department.

71
00:05:06,907 --> 00:05:08,967
And are you going
to fire us if we don't?

72
00:05:09,042 --> 00:05:11,841
I was just asking for your help.

73
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:19,852
The last time I checked the ER, you
had the best-kept charts in the building.

74
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:24,085
Last time I checked the 4th-floor
janitor's closet, I found House's charts.

75
00:05:24,191 --> 00:05:26,057
He hasn't filed
anything since you left.

76
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:29,290
Now, House may not care whether this
hospital's accreditation gets downgraded,

77
00:05:29,396 --> 00:05:33,265
but the people who sign my
paychecks do. So, I repeat: Current. Past.

78
00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:35,096
He doesn't have a current case.

79
00:05:35,202 --> 00:05:37,467
Did he tell you about the limo?

80
00:05:37,938 --> 00:05:40,965
So, I just press this button
every time I see a light?

81
00:05:41,074 --> 00:05:43,202
Tells me where
your blind spots are.

82
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:46,744
So, the twins,

83
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,225
they're going to turn out
to be yours, aren't they?

84
00:05:49,249 --> 00:05:52,048
I told you, I can't
talk about that stuff.

85
00:05:52,586 --> 00:05:55,146
But you want to be
done with this, right?

86
00:05:57,224 --> 00:05:59,284
One's mine, one's Julio's.

87
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,394
I knew it!

88
00:06:02,329 --> 00:06:06,061
Julio knocked her up before her
appendix burst. You got her after.

89
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:08,559
How can you watch that stuff?

90
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:10,100
Because it's awesome.

91
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:13,800
It's preposterous, not one real
moment since I've been on the show.

92
00:06:13,907 --> 00:06:18,345
As opposed to shows that represent
the world exactly the way it is, like...

93
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:20,342
Can't think of any.

94
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,071
What's going on?

95
00:06:22,282 --> 00:06:26,777
Hospital is being inspected, and Cuddy
dispatched you to keep an eye on me.

96
00:06:27,954 --> 00:06:30,150
I just parked a Town
Car in an ambulance bay,

97
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:33,591
and instead of ripping me one,
Cuddy acted like she didn't know me.

98
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,925
It's either an inspection
or an aneurysm.

99
00:06:35,996 --> 00:06:37,089
What's the test say?

100
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,955
As I suspected,

101
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:43,429
you have significant losses in the
upper right quadrant of your visual field.

102
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:44,503
Are you serious?

103
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:45,766
No, it's a joke.

104
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:47,534
Two guys go into a bar,

105
00:06:47,641 --> 00:06:50,753
and one has significant losses in the
upper right quadrant of his visual field.

106
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:53,144
The other one says
you're going to need an MRI

107
00:06:53,213 --> 00:06:55,273
to confirm the type and
location of the tumor.

108
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:57,442
That readout says
his vision's fine.

109
00:06:57,517 --> 00:06:58,541
No, it doesn't.

110
00:06:58,618 --> 00:06:59,642
Yes, it does.

111
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:01,950
You lied to me?

112
00:07:02,022 --> 00:07:05,322
I kidnapped you, and you're
surprised that I lied to you?

113
00:07:06,026 --> 00:07:08,723
It just means that the
symptoms are intermittent.

114
00:07:08,828 --> 00:07:11,491
You come near me
again, I'm calling the police.

115
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:14,398
You kidnapped him?

116
00:07:14,501 --> 00:07:17,665
It's sweet that I haven't lost
the ability to surprise you.

117
00:07:26,179 --> 00:07:27,477
Are you mocking me?

118
00:07:27,547 --> 00:07:29,209
My back. My back is killing me.

119
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,511
Don't care. Busy.

120
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:32,074
Amber's damn mattress.

121
00:07:32,152 --> 00:07:34,712
Well, that sucks.
Don't buy a new one.

122
00:07:35,522 --> 00:07:37,889
Are you being sarcastic?
Because we are buying one.

123
00:07:37,991 --> 00:07:40,017
She's incapable of doing
anything that matters

124
00:07:40,093 --> 00:07:42,562
without turning it
into a zero-sum game.

125
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:44,825
We're buying a mattress. For us.

126
00:07:44,898 --> 00:07:47,367
Wow, I'm faster
than you right now.

127
00:07:51,871 --> 00:07:56,536
It's all about her and whatever hapless
salesman wanders into her sights.

128
00:07:57,110 --> 00:08:01,514
She's going to lie, steal and trade
your testes to get whatever she wants.

129
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:06,885
Hold on. Just got to do something
before he dials the second "one."

130
00:08:10,757 --> 00:08:14,057
You're going to end up
humiliated, holding her purse

131
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:17,897
and going home to sleep
on a new mattress you hate.

132
00:08:17,964 --> 00:08:19,489
What the hell are you doing?

133
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:20,761
He needs a MRI.

134
00:08:22,802 --> 00:08:26,068
Give me one-millimeter
slices from the cortex down.

135
00:08:26,606 --> 00:08:29,906
Any particular reason you
decided to sedate a patient

136
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:31,911
for a procedure that's
completely painless?

137
00:08:32,278 --> 00:08:35,771
Guy has a history of violent
outbursts during surgical procedures.

138
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:37,283
Yeah, on TV.

139
00:08:38,284 --> 00:08:41,254
It's Evan Greer. He's the
main stud on House's soap.

140
00:08:41,321 --> 00:08:43,620
Frontal cortex looks
clean. No tumors.

141
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,819
Increase the magnification
on the occipital lobe.

142
00:08:47,494 --> 00:08:50,259
You watch because
you like or because I like?

143
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:52,063
I was unemployed. I...

144
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:55,801
Sorry, that's not an
answer, that's an apology.

145
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,647
If we are ever to come out of the
darkness, we have to be proud...

146
00:08:58,671 --> 00:09:01,869
Occipital, frontal and temporal
lobes are clean, so is the optic nerve.

147
00:09:01,975 --> 00:09:03,773
Definitely no tumors.

148
00:09:05,812 --> 00:09:06,812
He's fine?

149
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,314
And awake.

150
00:09:11,017 --> 00:09:12,485
What should we tell him?

151
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:16,216
See if you can talk
him out of suing me.

152
00:09:19,726 --> 00:09:21,786
He kidnapped me! He drugged me!

153
00:09:21,861 --> 00:09:23,625
Perhaps you should
go out the back way.

154
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,624
I'm not going anywhere
you people tell me to go.

155
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:30,565
It's just someone of your
fame... I figured fans...

156
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:33,970
You're trying to hide me. You
don't want me making a scene.

157
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,668
The hospital is
being inspected today.

158
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,404
And you want me
to do you a favor?

159
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:40,639
Not us, our dean of medicine.
And House hates her.

160
00:09:40,713 --> 00:09:43,205
You'd be doing House
a favor by complaining.

161
00:09:44,317 --> 00:09:45,317
Oh.

162
00:09:47,854 --> 00:09:50,688
This hospital is staffed
with lunatics and criminals.

163
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,988
Excuse me, where is Dr. Cuddy?

164
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:54,593
You okay?

165
00:09:54,661 --> 00:09:56,493
It's my foot. What
did he do to me?

166
00:09:56,563 --> 00:09:57,563
What did House do?

167
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:59,292
Nothing. I was with
him the whole time.

168
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:01,197
It's numb. I can't feel it.

169
00:10:05,839 --> 00:10:07,273
I can't walk.

170
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:15,779
Foot numbness has
a huge differential.

171
00:10:15,882 --> 00:10:20,582
That gets a lot narrower when you
add in peripheral-vision problems.

172
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:24,417
Which gets a lot wider when there's
no proof he ever had a vision problem.

173
00:10:24,524 --> 00:10:26,035
So House was wrong
about the first symptom,

174
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:27,459
but the guy just
happened to develop

175
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,859
a second, unrelated
symptom a few hours later?

176
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:32,455
He already kidnapped and
sedated the guy against his will.

177
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:35,899
Makes sense he'd also do something
to numb his foot so he couldn't leave.

178
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:39,064
But it doesn't make sense to
include a symptom that he caused

179
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:41,472
in a differential he's
so desperate to solve.

180
00:10:41,541 --> 00:10:43,203
Unless he didn't
mean to cause it.

181
00:10:43,276 --> 00:10:46,610
Stick to the filing, sweetheart.
Let the doctors do the doctoring.

182
00:10:46,713 --> 00:10:48,341
Either toxins or
vitamin deficiency...

183
00:10:48,414 --> 00:10:49,525
I'm guessing, when
you drugged him,

184
00:10:49,549 --> 00:10:51,882
you didn't catch him
and ease him to the floor.

185
00:10:52,085 --> 00:10:54,130
He could've pinched a
nerve in his ankle when he fell.

186
00:10:54,154 --> 00:10:56,783
You need to run an EMG
test for motor nerve entrapment

187
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:59,052
or the inspector
will own your ass.

188
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,891
Kutner, leave the
room, wait 30 minutes,

189
00:11:02,962 --> 00:11:05,295
come back and tell her
the test was negative.

190
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:07,993
Is it okay if I use that
time to do the test?

191
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:09,558
Get out of here.

192
00:11:09,636 --> 00:11:12,162
And the rest of them can
help me with all this stuff.

193
00:11:12,272 --> 00:11:14,571
They're busy, which
is really annoying,

194
00:11:14,641 --> 00:11:16,681
because I wanted to be
able to say that they're busy

195
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:18,836
for no other reason
than to screw with you.

196
00:11:19,445 --> 00:11:20,674
Research.

197
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,118
So the nut job was right?

198
00:11:25,785 --> 00:11:27,253
Usually is.

199
00:11:28,588 --> 00:11:30,318
He said I was dying.

200
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:34,989
He's wrong a lot, too.
That's why we do these tests.

201
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:38,656
Bet it's cool, you know,
being the star of a hit TV show?

202
00:11:39,465 --> 00:11:43,163
It's a daytime soap. It pretty much
puts me one step above dinner theater.

203
00:11:43,269 --> 00:11:45,033
Come on, you're on TV every day.

204
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:48,164
And who cares what the
critics think? Women love soaps.

205
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:52,837
You get to take pride in your job,
feel good when you go home at night.

206
00:11:52,946 --> 00:11:55,074
You're entertaining people.

207
00:11:55,148 --> 00:11:56,172
I don't care.

208
00:11:56,516 --> 00:11:58,542
Then you've made a
strange career choice.

209
00:11:58,651 --> 00:12:00,552
Look, I'm pandering.

210
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:03,953
I want to be part of
something that inspires people.

211
00:12:04,023 --> 00:12:07,892
So, quit. Find something
inspiring and do it.

212
00:12:07,994 --> 00:12:09,394
It's not that easy.

213
00:12:09,462 --> 00:12:10,486
Why not?

214
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:14,833
Just isn't.

215
00:12:19,505 --> 00:12:22,600
<i>It's my heart,
Doctor. It's racing.</i>

216
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:25,604
<i>I'm sure it's nothing. You're
a healthy woman, Marie.</i>

217
00:12:26,045 --> 00:12:28,207
<i>Shouldn't you examine me?</i>

218
00:12:29,349 --> 00:12:30,874
<i>Why don't you have Rico do it?</i>

219
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:34,011
You can't tell me you
didn't notice that pause.

220
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,581
Sorry.

221
00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:37,691
<i>She's never waking up.</i>

222
00:12:38,224 --> 00:12:41,251
This is a whole new
experience in super hi-def.

223
00:12:41,361 --> 00:12:43,762
I had no idea Marie
wore an underwire.

224
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:45,855
It does sound a little forced.

225
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:49,198
Could be stiffening in his tongue,
which is a symptom of myxedema.

226
00:12:49,269 --> 00:12:54,230
It's not the tongue. It's the dialogue.
I think I dated that nurse, though.

227
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:58,234
No.

228
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:01,278
What about the way he's
holding that stethoscope?

229
00:13:01,381 --> 00:13:04,044
The thumb and forefinger
are meeting at an odd angle.

230
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:06,609
Could be a demyelination
from toxic exposure.

231
00:13:06,719 --> 00:13:08,085
Back it up.

232
00:13:09,722 --> 00:13:11,020
What's this, the AV Club?

233
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:13,650
It's diagnostic.
Everything's under control.

234
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:17,788
Yeah, excellent job
so far. House, outside.

235
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,665
Keep watching.

236
00:13:21,768 --> 00:13:25,102
You'll never guess what
Rico's got in that box.

237
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:27,663
<i>Rico doesn't even
know I'm alive.</i>

238
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:31,676
You have an obsession with an actor
or the character he plays. I feel for you.

239
00:13:31,778 --> 00:13:34,270
You need to work it out.
But I need you to do it

240
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:38,148
when the hospital's accreditation,
and my job, are not on the line.

241
00:13:38,251 --> 00:13:42,245
You want the star of the hottest daytime
